# POUNDS TO DOLLARS
# Write a program that converts British pounds to US dollars formatted to the 3th decimal point.
# 1 British Pound = 1.31 Dollars

# SOLUTION
# Read how many ponds we need to convert to dollard from the console.

pounds = int(input())

# Multiply the pounds by 1.31 to receive the amount in dollars.

dollars = pounds * 1.31

# Round up the result to the third decimal place and print it out.

print(f'{dollars:.3f}')
